BT /F1 10 Tf 54 688 Td (Methods & Validation  -  GLP-1 FAERS Study) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 667 Td (Summary) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 653 Td (This document summarizes the ETL, analysis, and validation steps implemented for the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 639 Td (GLP-1 FAERS adverse-event study \(FAERS 2023Q1-2026Q1\).) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 618 Td (1\) Data ingestion & ETL) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 604 Td (- Source: FDA FAERS ASCII quarterly zip files \(DEMO, DRUG, REAC, OUTC, THER\).) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 590 Td (- Input ordering: FAERS_ZIP_LIST environment variable or FAERS_DIR lookup.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 576 Td (- Per-quarter processing: read tables, normalize primaryid/caseid, deduplicate DEMO per-) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 562 Td (quarter \(keep latest caseversion/fda_dt\), tag GLP-1 & control drugs by active ingredient) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 548 Td (string matching, identify GI PTs using a conservative MedDRA term list.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 534 Td (- Global deduplication: after concatenating quarters, deduplicate by caseid keeping) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 520 Td (latest fda_dt \(to avoid double-counted reports across quarters\).) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 506 Td (- Output: `data/processed/fact_adverse_event.csv`, `data/processed/drug_records.csv`,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 492 Td (`data/processed/reaction_records.csv`.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 471 Td (2\) Key preprocessing choices & rationale) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 457 Td (- Drug matching: simple case-insensitive substring matching of `prod_ai` to identify) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 443 Td (GLP-1s and controls. This favors recall of brand/generic mentions in a noisy field.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 429 Td (- GI mapping: curated list of MedDRA PTs selected to reduce false positives in the PRR) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 415 Td (background. A `GI_BROAD` set is also available for sensitivity checks.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 401 Td (- Time-to-onset \(TTO\): computed from THER.start_dt parsed as YYYYMMDD when available;) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 387 Td (TTO filtered with bounds \(TTO_MIN_DAYS, TTO_MAX_DAYS\) to remove implausible intervals.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 373 Td (- Missing values: Median imputation for `age_yr` and `wt_kg` grouped by `sex_clean` ×) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 359 Td (`cohort`, with fallback to global median. This preserves group medians and avoids model) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 345 Td (collapse due to NaNs.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 324 Td (3\) EDA & statistical testing) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 310 Td (- Descriptives: cohort counts, percent female, median age/weight, quarterly trends.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 296 Td (- Chi-Square test: 2×2 contingency \(GLP-1 vs control × GI severe vs not\). Cramér's V) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 282 Td (calculated for effect size.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 268 Td (- PRR: computed as \(a/\(a+b\)\) / \(c/\(c+d\)\) with Wald 95% CI on log\(PRR\). WHO-UMC signal) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 254 Td (criteria used: PRR >= 2, chi^2 >= 4, n >= 3.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 240 Td (- Mann-Whitney U: used for weight comparisons due to non-normal distribution.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 219 Td (4\) Data mining & modeling) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 205 Td (- Apriori: transaction = set of concurrent drugs \(top-N\) + outcome labels \(HOSPITALIZED,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 191 Td (GI_SEVERE_EVENT\). Parameters: min_support=0.02, min_confidence=0.40, min_lift=1.3.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 177 Td (- K-Means: features scaled with StandardScaler; silhouette method used to choose k;) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 163 Td (cluster profiling via medians and rates.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 149 Td (- Classification: Logistic Regression \(interpretable coefficients -> ORs\) and Random) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 135 Td (Forest \(high recall\). Feature engineering: log\(polypharmacy\), age×weight interaction,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 121 Td (label encoding for `glp1_drug`. Primary metric: recall \(sensitivity\) to minimize missed) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 107 Td (severe outcomes. RF cross-validation: 5-fold CV for AUC reporting.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 86 Td (5\) Validation & sensitivity checks) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 72 Td (- 5-fold CV performed for Random Forest AUC; reported mean ± std in) Tj ET
endstream
